def: One who maintains that faith alone, without works, issufficient for justification; -- opposed to nullifidian. Hammond.

The quality of being foreign; remoteness; want of relation orappropriateness.Let not the foreignness of the subject hinder you from endeavoring toset me right. Locke.A foreignness of complexion. G. Eliot.
A leguminous plant (Ornithopus scorpides) of Southern Europe,having curved pods.
In a manner not becoming to a guest. [R.] Milton.
The state or quality of being infrangible; infrangibility.
A kind of pessary of medicated wool or cotton, formerly used.
